Students analytical and selective skills are enhanced together with concrete working skills. 
Students also learn to adjust their individualities to concrete situation and to finalise their inspiration in a finished piece.
Students create larger dance works, learn to develope their own original dance language, and work with a scenario. 
Troughout the course students analytical skills are developed. The course prepares students for their graduation work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aims of the subject: - Knowledge about the rules, methods and different conceptual outputs of dance composition; ability to apply this knowledge in practical works; - Designing a suitable ground for shaping students; courage for creation and personal working skills; -The development into a creative person and the implementation of individual creativeness.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  -Demonstrates different alternatives for finding and selecting movements

-Is able to use choreographic material to carry out her/his idea for performance.

-Carries out the finalization of a dance with a dancer/dancers for a public performance (repetitor work)

-Composes and presents dance performace.
